snippet.title: Kwaxabana Oxamu | arr. Barrett and Ndlovu
snippet.description:
Kwaxabana Oxamu is arranged for TTBB voices and djembe. 

Kwaxabana Oxamu is a celebration of the isiXhosa language. It uses the various click sounds found in the Xhosa language to a stunning effect. The language will be a challenge, but the work will be well worth it for the end result! 

Purchase the music: https://giamusic.com/resource/kwaxabana-oxamu-ttbb-print-ww1841

Also available for SATB voicing: https://giamusic.com/resource/kwaxabana-oxamu-satb-print-ww1840
